Follow the instructions below to compile.  Use the same local maven repository to compile the modules so that the dependent jar files are not downloaded from the remote maven repo.

GFv3 modules:
============
1. cd v3
2. remove the following module in v3/pom.xml:
    admingui, distributions, registration, tests, embedded,
3. mvn -Dmaven.repo.local=<local maven repository> install 


HK2 (https://hk2.dev.java.net):
==============================
1. cd hk2
2. mvn -Dmaven.repo.local=<local maven repository> install 


JSP (https://jsp.dev.java.net):
==============================
1. cd jsp
2. mvn -Dmaven.repo.local=<local maven repository> install 


UEL (https://uel.dev.java.net):
==============================
1. cd uel
2. mvn -Dmaven.repo.local=<local maven repository> install 


Grizzly (https://grizzly.dev.java.net):
======================================
1. cd grizzly
2. mvn -Dmaven.repo.local=<local maven repository> install


jsf-api (https://javaserverfaces.dev.java.net):
==============================================
1. cd jsf/mojarra
2. modify build.properties:  jsf.build.home=SOURCE_HOME where SOURCE_HOME is <glassfish-ri>/jsf
3. cd jsf/jsf-api
4. ant -f build.xml
   The jsp-api.jar file is located in: <glassfish-ri>/jsf/build/lib/jsf-api.jar
5. modify jsf-api-pom.xml: 
    <distributionManagement>
        <repository>
            <id>java.net-m2-repository</id>
            <url>java-net:/maven2-repository/trunk/www/repository/</url>
        </repository>
    </distributionManagement>
    change <url>...</url> to your local maven repository.
   e.g. <url>file:/export/home/GlassFish/jsf/repository</url>
6. ant push-to-maven



glassfish-corba (https://glassfish-corba.dev.java.net/design/orb_notes.html#htoc7):
==================================================================================
1. cd glassfish-corba/make
2. ant rename
3. cd glassfish-corba/build/rename/ee/make
4. ant build
5. cd glassfish-corba/make
6. ant make-bundles
7. ant -Drepo.url="file:<local-maven-repo>" -Drelease.version=3.0.0 -Dbuild.version=b001  release

